      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. it's pretty heavy on the morality which is exactly what i need. can u expand on that part about how the current system is basically just \"inheriting prejudice\"? like, how can we argue that meritocracy is actually just a cover for these racial inequities? i want to show that the idea of \"working hard for what you get\" is kind of a myth in this context.",
