      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of pure meritocracy functions as a powerful ideological veil, masking the structural barriers that disproportionately affect marginalized racial groups. When systemic racism limits access to quality education, capital, and safe environments, the playing field is demonstrably uneven from the start. Consequently, claims of \"hard work\" become insufficient explanations for vastly different life outcomes, effectively rebranding inherited systemic disadvantage as personal failure. To admit this is to challenge the very myth that underpins modern capitalist fairness.",
      "source": "target",
