      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's intense, i like that phrasing. \"the myth that underpins modern capitalist fairness\" is a really strong line. \n\ncan you help me write a concluding paragraph for this section? i want it to basically hammer home that any argument for maintaining the status quo—like people saying we should just focus on \"equality of opportunity\" instead of redistribution—is basically just a way to ignore the reality of racial injustice. i want it to feel like the only logical/moral conclusion is that redistribution is the only way forward.",
