      "content": "Ultimately, prioritizing mere \"equality of opportunity\" feels like a semantic trick, as it tacitly agrees to uphold a rigged game. Focusing solely on individual effort ignores the massive, inherited disadvantages woven into the very fabric of our society. Until comprehensive wealth redistribution directly addresses these crystallized, racialized inequalities, the promise of meritocracy remains a dangerously convenient fiction. The only pathway toward genuine justice is one that actively recalibrates economic power away from entrenched privilege.",
